d second-generation force field. Interestingly,\nin the low-frequency regime also force fields with a rather simplistic model\nfor the bonding interactions (like the General Amber Force Field) perform\nrather well. As far as the tested DFTB parametrization is concerned, we obtain\na significant underestimation of the unit cell volume resulting in a pronounced\noverestimation of the phonon energies in the low frequency region. This cannot\nbe mended by relying on the DFT-calculated unit cell, since with this unit cell\nthe DFTB phonon frequencies significantly underestimate the experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Feb 2020 09:55:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 6 Apr 2020 10:22:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-07"}
